article.headline: Niagara 88, St. Peter's 55
article.story: LEWISTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Charron Fisher scored 23 points to lead Niagara in an 88-55 win over St. Peter's Wednesday. The Purple Eagles (7-7 overall, 2-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) have won six of seven after a 1-6 start. The Peacocks (3-10, 1-2) have lost five straight. Niagara shot 55.4 percent from the floor. J.R. Duffey and Lorenzo Miles each finished with 16 points. Clif Brown had 11 points and 10 rebounds. The Peacocks shot 37.9 percent from the floor (25 for 66). St. Peter's also shot 2-for-8 from the free throw line, missing all six attempts in the second half. Niagara hit 14 of 15 free throws. The Purple Eagles opened a 22-6 lead in the first nine minutes on J.R. Duffey's third 3-pointer and led 47-26 at the half. Tim Spitler had 15 points to lead St. Peter's. Akeem Gooding added 10 points and 11 rebounds. The Peacocks played shorthanded as Todd Sowell and Michael Gore did not travel with the team due to violation of team policy, coach John Dunne said.
